{
  "stem": "25912.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In the morning, as spies, they decided to put us in the hands of the field police, military field police, in another neighboring village.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I can't remember where it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In any case, here we struck lucky, because it happened to have been a unit which came back from England.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were part of the [? free ?] Czechs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we told them the truth.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, there was no way we would have gotten away [? with. ?] And they were wonderful.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They gave up their beds in the barracks for our little group.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they said, OK..",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They can't get us to Linz, but they will give us a train pass to go to Pilsen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Because at that time, Pilsen was in joint hands of the Russians and the Americans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They said, you've got to get there in the next three days before the Americans move out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You'll be all right on the train with this pass, but not in Prague.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we had to change trains in Prague.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In Prague, they won't take any notice of this safe conduct, or whatever you call it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we traveled on the train to Prague.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somehow, I don't know how, we managed to change stations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we got to Pilsen, where again, six o'clock in the morning, November, strange city.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, how are you going to ask, where are the Americans?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we just wandered around the town till we saw there was a hotel with an American MP on guard outside, which was a fantastic relief.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we went in and sat down there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were very lucky, because it turned out that there was a Polish Repatriation Mission in that hotel.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
